			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="color: blue">(Already posted in the Epic 1.5 forum -- just posting here for the sake of completeness)
<br />
</span>
<br />
I decided to put together a checklist for wizards to use while trying to obtain their epic 1.5 (and already have epic 1.0, or have done the quest to skip epic 1.0). (Not like we have any wizards left who don't have this info, but I had already done half of this so /shrug)
<br />

<br />
It's mostly ripped from the epic guide on graffe's <a href="http://www.graffe.com/library/epic/" target="_blank" class="postlink">http://www.graffe.com/library/epic/</a>, but it is in checklist format and has some additional information that either doesn't exist or isn't really explained well in the guide. 
<br />

<br />
N.B. The CODE block below this checklist is the actual code used to create this list - you can copy and paste this into your own post to create your own checklist.
<br />

<br />
<ol type="1">
<br />
<li> [ ] [SOLO] Hail <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=15998" target="_blank" class="postlink">Talwyn Flamecaller</a> in Lava Storm Mountains (-2170, -1050). Say each of the following in order to get the proper character flags: What fluxing rod?, What fluxing gem?, What fluxing rune?, and What fluxing ore?
<br />
<li> [ ] [SOLO] Obtain <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=30811" target="_blank" class="postlink">A Fluxing Chunk of Ore</a>, a ground spawn in Ruined City of Dranik at the rat caves (1360, -337)
<br />
<li> [ ] [SOLO] Obtain a <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=32486" target="_blank" class="postlink">Prysmatic Crystal</a>, a ground spawn in Twilight Sea (4269,1223)
<br />
<li> [ ] [SOLO] Obtain a <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=32487" target="_blank" class="postlink">Prysmatic Crystal</a>, a ground spawn in Veksar (300, 350)	
<br />
<li> [ ] [SOLO] Obtain a <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=32488" target="_blank" class="postlink">Prysmatic Crystal</a>, a ground spawn in Timorous Deep (5613, -4228)
<br />
<li> [ ] [SOLO] Obtain a <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=30352" target="_blank" class="postlink">Prysmatic Crystal</a> from <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=11239" target="_blank" class="postlink">Treasure Sorter Neiben</a> in Dulak ( <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=15484" target="_blank" class="postlink">A Shady Treasure Sorter</a> are place holders, so kill all the ones found around -75, -877 to get him to spawn if he is not up)
<br />
<li> [ ] [SOLO] Obtain a <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=23775" target="_blank" class="postlink">Cohesion Gem</a> from trash mob's in Plane of Innovation (drops off almost every mob)
<br />
<li> [ ] [SOLO] Obtain 130 in Tailoring
<br />
 <ul>
<br />
 <li> To get to 54 Tailoring for free, use the quest <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=2887" target="_blank" class="postlink">Tailoring Freebie: Tonlyei's Chores</a>, given by Tonlyei Lyhin (+45, +145) in Absymal Sea
<br />
 <li> You will need some small amount of Smithing to advance in Tailoring later, so to get to 54 Smithing for free, use the quest <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=2831" target="_blank" class="postlink">Smithing Freebie: Help Snokin</a>, given by Snokin Breaksteel (+95, +275) in Absymal Sea
<br />
 <li> For all patterns listed below, you can buy them from Tonlyei Lyhin (+45, +145) in Absymal Sea or from Higwyn Matrick (120, 1480 at the western trader building) in Plane of Knowledge
<br />
 <li> To get to 66 Tailoring, buy a bunch of Mandrake Root from Severg ODanos (-20, 1375 at the western trader building) in Plane of Knowledge - combine 2 Mandrake Root to make Woven Mandrake - save the Woven Mandrake for next step
<br />
 <li> To get to 76 Tailoring, use your uber Smithing skills to make <a href="http://eqtraders.com/items/show_item.php?item=1137" target="_blank" class="postlink">Steel Boning</a> and combine 1 Steel Boning and 1 Woven Mandrake to make a Picnic Basket
<br />
 <li> To get to 88 Tailoring, buy up 20 or 30 <a href="http://eqtraders.com/items/show_item.php?item=1546" target="_blank" class="postlink">Greyhopper Hide</a>'s from the bazaar (or kill greyhoppers in Marus Seru for them), and buy the same amount of glove patterns . Combine Greyhopper Hide and glove pattern to make Greyhopper Hide Gloves
<br />
 <li> From here on we will need alot of <a href="http://eqtraders.com/items/show_item.php?item=2146" target="_blank" class="postlink">Crystalline Silk Swatches</a>, which are made by combining 2 <a href="http://eqtraders.com/items/show_item.php?item=1306" target="_blank" class="postlink">Crystalline Silk</a>. You will need somewhere around 130 Crystalline Silk Swatches to finish up, and you can usually find both the silks and the swatches in the bazaar (or kill spiders in Velketor's Labyrinth for the silks). You will also need around 100 or so <a href="http://eqtraders.com/items/show_item.php?item=2603" target="_blank" class="postlink">Silver Thread's</a> which can be bought from Tonlyei Lyhin (+45, +145) in Absymal Sea
<br />
 <li> To get to 102 Tailoring, combine crystalline silk swatch, silver thread, and gorget pattern to make Crystalline Silk Collar
<br />
 <li> To get to 115 Tailoring, combine crystalline silk swatch, silver thread, and cap pattern to make Crystalline Silk Cap
<br />
 <li> To get to 124 Tailoring, combine (2) crystalline silk swatch, silver thread, and glove pattern to make Crystalline Silk Gloves
<br />
 <li> To get to 131 Tailoring, combine (3) crystalline silk swatch, silver thread, and tunic pattern to make Crystalline Silk Shirt
<br />
 </ul> 
<br />
<li> [ ] [1 GROUP] Obtain a <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=30543" target="_blank" class="postlink">Wisp of Pure Flame</a> from the Pure Flame Elemental at the end of the ring event in The Carvern of Exiles (Solusek Dungeon C) 
<br />
 <ul>
<br />
 <li> Static spawn at end of ring event, no spawn timer
<br />
 <li> Bring yourself, a chanter, tank, healer, and whatever else you can get (some dps is good)
<br />
 <li> To get to Sol C (if you've forgotten like I had), zone into Sol B. Look on the map for "CE Zone", thats the zone in for Cavern of Exiles. Levitate everyone, and train your way there. When you zone into CE, zone in while swimming in the lava, or else you will be zoned into Sol A. And if you try to zone back to Sol B from Sol A, you will actually zone into Cavern of Exiles, but on the wrong side. Got it? Good.
<br />
 <li> Upon zoning in from Sol B side, fight south until you get to the room just north of the room where the bridges form a lambda symbol (upside down Y). Put another way, the two circular rooms at the south end of the middle of the zone. (guide has handy map for this)
<br />
 <li> The room in question is a circular room with lava in the center. There will be 8 lava elementals in the area, 4 Lava Vindicators and 4 Lava Champions. Kill these and 1 minute later four Furious Magma Guardians will spawn. Kill these and 1 minute later two Inflamed Champions will spawn. Kill these and 1 minute later the Pure Flame Elemental spawns.
<br />
 <li> Pure Flame Elemental mitigates slow, hits soft, and has no ae
<br />
 </ul>
<br />
<li> [ ] [1 GROUP] Obtain a <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=33236" target="_blank" class="postlink">Shard of Pure Ice</a> from the <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=12973" target="_blank" class="postlink">Mistress of the Darkwater</a> in Sirens Grotto
<br />
 <ul>
<br />
 <li> Static spawn, unknown spawn timer (was up everytime i checked)
<br />
 <li> Bring yourself, a chanter, tank, healer, and whatever else you can get (some dps is good)
<br />
 <li> All the mobs are at most dark blue cons to level 70, this stuff should not present any problem to a halfway decent group
<br />
 <li> From the succor point in Siren's Grotto, run out and around until you get to an area with water. To your left will be a building with a well in it. Swim down to the bottom of the well. You will now be in a larger pool of water. Swim away from the well and then up to get out of the water. This area has many Sirens in it, including the enchanter epic mob (doesn't see invisibility). At the very top of the ramp is the Mistress.
<br />
 <li> Go up the platform to the level just below her, clear out the area, then pull her. She brings a few along with her, but they are mezzed/killed/tanked easily.
<br />
 <li> Mistress of Darkwater is not slowable, hits for 500ish, and has an ae: <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=3784&source=Live&setcookie=1" target="_blank" class="postlink">Drowning Panic</a> (disease resist: 100hp dot, slow 15%, range 150)
<br />
 </ul>
<br />
<li> [ ] [2 GROUPS] Obtain <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=30810" target="_blank" class="postlink">A Fluxing Rune</a> from <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=16357" target="_blank" class="postlink">Hob Goblin Horrorfiend</a> in Plane of Nightmare 
<br />
 <ul>
<br />
 <li> Static spawn, 1 hour spawn timer
<br />
 <li> He is located at the back of the Hobgoblin caves. Just fight your way thru to him.
<br />
 <li> Hobgoblin Horrorfiend is slowable, hits for 200-400 usually, with some hits in mid 1000's, and has an ae: <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=4117&source=Live" target="_blank" class="postlink">Flames of the Fiend</a> (chromatic resist: 2500 nuke, range 400)
<br />
 </ul>
<br />
<li> [ ] [5 GROUPS] Obtain <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=33234" target="_blank" class="postlink">A Fluxing Staff</a> from the <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=16144" target="_blank" class="postlink">Girplan Guardian</a> in Wall of Slaughter 
<br />
 <ul>
<br />
 <li> Static spawn, 1-3 hour spawn timer
<br />
 <li> Have the tank pin him against the NE cubby in the room with the Crystalline Portal
<br />
 <li> Girplan Guardian is slowable, ae rampages, hits for 2300, and has 2 ae's: <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=5702&source=Live" target="_blank" class="postlink">Curse of Misfortune</a> (magic resist: physical damage -50%, range 500) and <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=4430&source=Live" target="_blank" class="postlink">Cessation of Health</a> (poison resist, 750 dot, 400 range)
<br />
 </ul>
<br />
<li> [ ] [5 GROUPS] Obtain <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=16194" target="_blank" class="postlink">A Fluxing Gem</a> from the <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=16194" target="_blank" class="postlink">Elite Sun Revenant</a> in The Scarlet Desert 
<br />
 <ul>
<br />
 <li> Static spawn, 12 hour timer (?), must say 'I have come for your gems' while sitting in and/or around the cauldron on the plateau that is surrounded by aliens. To get inside the cauldron use levitate and bard / horse speed to run from the highest rock nearby.
<br />
 <li> Note: make a macro to spam the text, as you have to mess around with getting the exact spot to say the text. Also, if ESR is up when you arrive, you can usually spawn him again right away. But I believe when you spawn him, you have to wait 12 hours to spawn again. 
<br />
 <li> This is a ranged fight, no pets. Send tank out and have everyone else fight out of range of the dot's.
<br />
 <li> Elite Sun Revenant is slowable, flurries, hits for mid 1000's, has 2 ae's: <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=4488&source=Live" target="_blank" class="postlink">Greater Sand Curse of Knowledge</a> (unresistable, spell haste -50%, 1000 mana dot, range 150) and <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=4487&source=Live" target="_blank" class="postlink">Greater Sand Curse of Life</a> (prismatic resist: 1000hp dot, -500 atk, range 150), and 1 nasty melee proc: <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=5676&source=Live" target="_blank" class="postlink">Torment of Body</a> (3000hp nuke, 300hp dot, -25% accuracy, -100 casting levels)
<br />
 </ul>
<br />
<li> [ ] [SOLO] Return to Talwyn Flamecaller in Lava Storm Mountains (-2170, -1050)
<br />
 <ul>
<br />
 <li> Hand Talwyn A Fluxing Gem, A Fluxing Rune, A Fluxing Ore, and A Fluxing Staff to receive the <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=33235" target="_blank" class="postlink">Staff of Fluxing Power</a>
<br />
 <li> Hand Talwyn the Shard of Pure Ice, and he will hand it back to you 
<br />
 <li> Hand Talwyn the Wisp of Pure Flame, and he will hand it back to you
<br />
 </ul>
